+### Story 9.13: Video Detection Tester
+
+**Status:** backlog (NEW 2026-05-15 via correct-course).
+**Summary:** New tool `apps/tooling/tools/video_test.py` (single-file shape — pure helpers + thin `main(argv) -> int`). Consumes an emitted `map_config.<hud_version>.json` and runs the full detection pipeline against a real video. CLI: `python tools/video_test.py <video.mp4> [--config <map_config.json>] [--output <results.json>]`. Pipeline: (a) i-frame extraction via `cv2.VideoCapture` + configurable stride; (b) once-per-session HUD-version classification via `hud_version_detection`; (c) per-i-frame binary `in_match` classification via `in_match_detection`; (d) state machine — `in_match` rising → `in_match` span; falling edge → `score_screen` for `score_screen_duration_ms`; then `not_in_match` (lobby+transition merged) until next rising edge; (e) map-ID classification on `in_match` spans via `minimap_identification` (weighted) — most-confident across span = canonical match label. Output `results.json` shape: top-level `hud_version` + ordered list of `{frame_idx, timestamp_ms, state ∈ {in_match, score_screen, not_in_match}}` + `matches: [{start_frame, end_frame, map_id, confidence}, ...]`. Reuses Tool 9's per-frame zone-fire logic (no reinvention). Pytest for pure logic + manual smoke test against ≥1 real EVA capture. `wardentooling.py` registers video_test. Dependencies: 9.9c (target schema + `score_screen_duration_ms`); ideally 9.12 (populated zone configs) + 9.14 (HUD-version classifier exercised on labeled PNGs). Sprint fit: fits-in-one-sprint (~2-3 days). Track C. Closes workflow step #6. See [`sprint-change-proposal-2026-05-15.md`](sprint-change-proposal-2026-05-15.md).
